      <hedline>
        <hl1>What Would the Founders Say?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dan Solomon letter on Michael Novak's Sept 4 article scores view that only monotheists possess civility</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Does Michael Novak (Op-Ed, Sept. 4) mean to say only monotheists possess civility and thus civilization and that all others are ''barbarians'' who, having ''to rely on clubs,'' are devoid of any sense of truth? If this is what he means by a ''constitutional space for religion in public,'' it is a very bad idea indeed.</p>
        <p>DAN SOLOMON  Poughkeepsie, N.Y., Sept. 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
